history.content:
Hello CS'ers!
 
While I know you're being inundated with surveys this time of year, the CS Advising survey is particularly impactful--not only for you--but for we advisors as well. Your survey responses have helped us leverage for more advisors (the addition of Lily & Charlene), more resources (peer advisors), and have informed us on how to better serve you (easy-to-book appointments, automating CPT so you don't need to visit 3 offices to complete it, and quite a bit more). Indicating where we do good work has helped us increase staffing while inspiring us to continue to serve you, and indicating areas of improvement has resulted in, well, a lot of improvement.
 
Please take a moment to ensure advising not only remains, but becomes stronger for future cohorts of students who are passionate about computer science. The individual advisor comments are especially helpful for our practice. If you have been meaning to stop by and say something, now's your opportunity to do so.
 
all the best,
 
Christopher
 
PS Here's the survey link again!
